fixes compatibility with macos big sur. (#47)

* fixes compatibility with macos big sur.

MacOS Big Sur had dynamic linker changes. Shared libraries are now
stored only in `/System/Library/dyld/dyld_shared_cache_x86_64`
and no longer present on the actual file system. This changes makes the
`find_library` not return the paths of the libraries such as
`find_library("ssl")`

* remove old/broken howsmyssl test

fixes compatibility with macos big sur. (#47)

* fixes compatibility with macos big sur.

MacOS Big Sur had dynamic linker changes. Shared libraries are now
stored only in `/System/Library/dyld/dyld_shared_cache_x86_64`
and no longer present on the actual file system. This changes makes the
`find_library` not return the paths of the libraries such as
`find_library("ssl")`

* remove old/broken howsmyssl test

commit.message: Fix an unuseful socket exception with OpenSSL on Mac

Only use LibreSSL on macOS 10.15 when fake OpenSSL is detected

This fixes issues where a real version of OpenSSL was found outside of
/usr/lib/.

Also, apply the patch to macOS 10.15+ so we don't need a new release for
macOS 10.16, etc.
Disable uploading coverage reports to codecov since it is a constant thorn in my side
Use DigiCert's revoked test domain since revoked.grc.com has expired
Fix an issue with running egg_info from an sdist
Run GitHub actions on pull requests
Update deps task to filter by python_version and requires_python
Version 1.2.0
Mark this as an in-development version

Allow re-calling use_ctypes(), use_openssl() and use_winlegacy()

Previously if these were called after any part of oscrypto had been
initialized it would be an error. Now as long as the configuration is
the same, they can be called multiple times. This can help ensure
config is consistent when there are different entry points into oscrypto
from an app that is configuring it.
